            <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng">
                <p>These are the footprints <supplied reason="explanation">tapak walar</supplied> of the one of praiseworthy asceticism. He, his majesty king Wastu, ruling in the city Kawali, is the one who beautifies the palace Surawisesa, who digs a moat around the city, who plants <supplied reason="explanation">crops</supplied> in all villages. If there is one in the future, he must do good works, so that success in the world be long-lasting.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="id">
            <note type="credit">Indonesian translation below is taken from <name>Titi Surti Nastiti</name> (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:TitiSurtiNastiti1996_01"/><citedRange>21</citedRange></bibl></note><!--Arlo: Is this the expected expression for explain the responsable of the translation? -->
                
                <p>Inilah tanda bekas beliau yang mulia Prabu Raja Wastu <supplied reason="subaudible">yang</supplied> berkuasa di kota Kawali yang memperindah keraton Surawisesa yang membuat parit <supplied reason="subaudible">di</supplied> sekeliling ibukota yang memakmurkan seluruh desa.</p> 
                <p>Semoga ada penerus raja yang melaksanakan berbuat kebajikan agar lama jaya di dunia.</p>
                </div>
            
