        <div type="bibliography">
	
<p>The inscription was initially read by Friederich (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:Friederich1855_01"/><citedRange>149–182</citedRange></bibl>), then by Holle (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:Holle1867_01"/><citedRange>464-470</citedRange></bibl>, Pleyte (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:Pleyte1911_03"/><citedRange>167-169</citedRange></bibl>. Noorduyn (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:Noorduyn1976_01"/></bibl>) made a significant contribution of readings through his report, but it is unfortunately not widely published. A close study was undertaken by Titi Surti Nastiti (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:TitiSurtiNastiti1996_01"/><citedRange>1-13</citedRange></bibl>) who furnish an Indonesian translation. Re-edited here by Aditia Gunawan &amp; Arlo Griffiths from our photos collection. In our apparatus, variant readings are cited from Holle, Pleyte, Noorduyn and Titi Surti Nastiti's editions.</p>
            
